{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, the leptonic Higgs bi-fermion operators C Hℓ are also strongly constrained, despite the ε H and ε L suppression factors.",
    "This is due to the expected improvement factor of approximately O(100) in the A ℓ EWPO at FCC-ee (see table 9).",
    "While current data are compatible with TeV-scale NP within this setup, leaving open the possibility of a quasi-natural solution to the EW hierarchy problem, our projections show that FCC-ee will be able to completely rule out this possibility or, from a more optimistic perspective, provide clear evidence for this NP framework.Future projections for operators most strongly probed by EWPO.",
    "We now proceed to a more general analysis, moving away from the third-generation NP scenario.",
    "We sort all operators based on the strength of current EW constraints and perform the FCC-ee projection, showing the results in figure 9.As expected, operators entering Z-pole observables at tree-level -those involving Higgses -receive extremely stringent bounds."
  ]
}